{
  "stem": "19111.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 216.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Kailis is a Lithuanian word that has to do with furs.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think it's fur, or fur is kailis.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so they designated the name of Kailis to that labor camp, and there were actually two big buildings, six or seven story buildings, next to each other, plus some-- a few other houses next to it that was all fenced in all around.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they closed off a gate with an entrance in there, and they formed some police among the Jewish people, as well as on the outside was the German watchmen.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they took all of the Jewish furriers-- not all, but for the most part-- into this place called Kailis labor camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Kailis.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Strictly a fur factory, right.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All they did was work on the fur coats and fur vests.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had-- later on, we still had a lot of connections with the ghetto because a lot of furriers were still living in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was not enough room for them in Kailis, and they had to still march back and forth to their work of place-- the place of work, and so we used to get all the news from the ghetto as time went on.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Every so often, [INAUDIBLE] actions, and they would take Jews away, 1,500, 2,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First men, and then women and children.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They used to take them, supposedly sent to another sent to another camp where they would do some work.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "People still didn't know that Ponary existed, that Jews are being taken to Lukiskes, and from there, they were sent.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We in turn were placed in Kailis.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were imprisoned, and we had rations with food that they gave us, which was very small.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
